><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=camcdad@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>camcdad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(12/12/03 1:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Taking the Boy to the Li'l Red</span><hr size=1> I am taking my 10 year old son to the Little Red next Thursday (Fishin' Friday and Saturday).  We will be wading and I am not sure where the best shot will be to put him on fish.  Mostly what I hear is Cow Shoals, but I wanted to check with the y'all.<br>
<br>
My son is a &quot;Dry Run Addict.&quot;  I need to get him to a river so &quot;wwweee&quot; can fish; not that I'm bitter<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I appreciate the help. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=flyfishar>FlyFishAR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 1020<br> <font color=#000000>(12/12/03 2:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.flyfishingarkansas.com/Photo%20Gallery/tn_j.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taking the Boy to the Li'l Red</span><hr size=1> They have built a kid's area on the Little Red now as well. It's called Collins creek and is in the camping area in JFK park. Another option is to fish close to the park. It is C&amp;R so be sure to fish barbless and release everything. You &quot;will&quot; get checked there. Cow Shoal is really crowded right now and woudn't really be a place to take a new fly fisher. The fish there can be really tough.<br>
<br>
John <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=camcdad@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>camcdad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#000000>(12/12/03 2:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taking the Boy to the Li'l Red</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the info.  My biggest desire is to move him from &quot;Dry Run&quot; expectations to enjoying a more realistic day on the river.  I am open to taking him to any of the rivers.  If the area around the campground is the best for that, I'm game.  I want him to have opportunities to get used to casting, wading carefully...etc.  Is there a better option on the White or Norfork?<br>
<br>
Mike <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=flyfishar>FlyFishAR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 1022<br> <font color=#000000>(12/12/03 6:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.flyfishingarkansas.com/Photo%20Gallery/tn_j.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taking the Boy to the Li'l Red</span><hr size=1> They are running alot of water on the White at the moment. If you are going camping you might consider either JFK park on the Little Red or the Norfork State Park camp ground. Actually the fishing has been pretty good at both the parks lately.<br>
<br>
John <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jimmyt@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>Jimmy T</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 422<br> <font color=#000000>(12/13/03 6:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taking the Boy to the Li'l Red</span><hr size=1> Where is the Norfork State Park Campground.  I think John means the C.O E. Campground at the Norfork.....Camp at the state park at Bull Shoals and drive him down in front of the water at Rim Shoals.  Heck pay Gary Flippin $3 bucks to ferry ya'll to the island and you can both fish.  Show up about 8 or 9 am.  Fish the back side of the island.  <br>
<br>
You could hire John or Troutstalker or Drifter or Stinniti and have a  really good day on the river.  Make 'em cook for ya' and start a fire to keep warm though.  Comes with the trip.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
You'd  and your son would learn a bunch in a hurry.  Nothing like a steep learning curve to end or start the Year.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Jimmy T. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=camcdad@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>camcdad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#000000>(12/13/03 9:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taking the Boy to the Li'l Red</span><hr size=1> Jimmy-Thanks for the help.  I have hacked around on the White and the Norfork the last 6 or 7 years and could definitely use some &quot;how to's.&quot;  I have a lot of bad habits I would like my son to avoid.<br>
<br>
How much do you think a 10 year old could pick up in a solid day?  And which river do you think would be the best suited?  I can't think of a better Christmas break trip than to hook a few, learn alot, and leave knowing enough to come back on our own<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  May be a tall order... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jimmyt@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>Jimmy T</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 425<br> <font color=#000000>(12/14/03 3:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taking the Boy to the Li'l Red</span><hr size=1> I think he could learn the following:<br>
<br>
Seeing fish, Drifts, Mending, casting without disturbing too many fish.  Iv'e seen John with kids and he is really good.  He has a boat now and is fishing the norfork today and tomarrow.<br>
<br>
The best river would be the one without water running in it.  You might even findyourself fishing two or even three rivers in one day.  Well mabey just two.   <br>
<br>
I have John's number  (Cell) 479-857-3438<br>
Troutstalker Ryan Walker Hm.  870-431-5012<br>
<br>
I've seen John with Kids before.  Your boy will have a good day and learn a whole bunch with either one of them.<br>
<br>
Not that I would not recomend Drifter or Stinitti but I've never fished with either one of them.  I do know that they are very competent.   Besides this way you get to fish and take picts.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maddog48>maddog48</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#000000>(12/15/03 6:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taking the Boy to the Li'l Red</span><hr size=1> I have to agree with Jimmy T on this one. I have seen John with youth, too and I am almost... almost<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  convinced he loves to teach as much as fish. If you want to start your son right, John's the way to go. He's very patient and understanding as well. Good luck. I think you and your son will definitely enjoy/learn from the experience. Nothing against the other guides mentioned here, but it's just that I've seen John work.<br>
<br>
<br>
Mike  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=21.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=21.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=21.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm10.threadControl?topicID=21.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=21.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=21.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub98.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowF